The paper deals with planning algorithms for Partially-Observable Markov Decision Processes (POMDPs) with continuous state, action, and observation spaces. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) for the POMDP problem, Robotics (cs.RO) for the hand-eye coordination domain, Machine Learning (cs.LG) for the use of Gaussian mixture and Extended Kalman Filter, Systems and Control (cs.SY) for the feedback control and state estimation, and Computer Vision (cs.CV) for the simulation of the hand-eye coordination domain.
